Replace '<SSH_PORT>' with the actual port number you use for SSH access.
Uncomment and customize the lines for any additional services you want to allow through the firewall by replacing '<SERVICE_PORT>' with the respective port numbers.
Uncomment or modify any other rules based on your specific requirements. For example, you can add specific rules to block or restrict access to certain IP addresses or IP ranges.
Save the script with a '.sh extension '(e.g., firewall.sh).'
Make the script executable with the command 'chmod '+x firewall.sh.'
Run the script with superuser privileges using 'sudo './firewall.sh.'
